<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Pauncefote</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Personal.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Newport R.
                                    I.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hill</hi>: I have received a telegram from
                            the Marquis of Salisbury in which he desires me to convey to the
                            Secretary of State the deep sympathy of Her Majesty’s Government on the
                            occasion of the terrible disaster at Galveston.</p>
                        <p>I take this opportunity of expressing my own sorrow at this calamitous
                            event.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>